{"id": "EUVD-2022-55748", "enisaUuid": "44ef4836-fbb8-3286-a146-047e8346043e", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nriscv: mm: add missing memcpy in kasan_init\n\nHi Atish,\n\nIt seems that the panic is due to the missing memcpy during kasan_init.\nCould you please check whether this patch is helpful?\n\nWhen doing kasan_populate, the new allocated base_pud/base_p4d should\ncontain kasan_early_shadow_{pud, p4d}'s content. Add the missing memcpy\nto avoid page fault when read/write kasan shadow region.\n\nTested on:\n - qemu with sv57 and CONFIG_KASAN on.\n - qemu with sv48 and CONFIG_KASAN on.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T18:30:30", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T18:30:30", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff0f6becf3a6f817838b6f80a2c9cca43dce0576", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9f2ac64d6ca60db99132e08628ac2899f956a0ec", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50657"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50657"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08241a9b-4215-361c-92ca-c597a08f151d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8fbdccd2b17335e1881a23865e98c63fcc345938 <9f2ac64d6ca60db99132e08628ac2899f956a0ec"}, {"id": "17cf075a-a8a0-32a9-a70a-54a962c70d54", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.18"}, {"id": "72dfd6ca-271a-381d-a2f4-38d87df53727", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8fbdccd2b17335e1881a23865e98c63fcc345938 <ff0f6becf3a6f817838b6f80a2c9cca43dce0576"}, {"id": "80cf7f1e-e077-3192-aea8-e241245bfe85", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "bfea6741-77b9-3d48-ab1b-b398b92c6961", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "f3864e4e-a1a5-3dde-a5da-d452057b75b4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.7"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "843f9379-061b-307c-8ceb-d8bc35be8439", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}